<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
  <metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  </metal:leftportlets>

  <div metal:fill-slot="help">
    <p>
      Here you see the information we have available about this language.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you see anything wrong with this information, please see whether it's
      already been brought up in the 
      <a tal:attributes="href view/answers_url">Answers</a> application.
       If not, please file a question there.
    </p>

    <ul class="info">
      <li>
        <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/RosettaFAQ"
        >Frequently asked questions</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
  </div>

  <div metal:fill-slot="main">
    <h1>Overview of
    <tal:has_nativename condition="context/nativename">
      <tal:nativename replace="context/nativename">
        Espa&ntilde;ol
      </tal:nativename> (
    </tal:has_nativename>
    <tal:englishname replace="context/englishname">Spain</tal:englishname>
    <tal:has_nativename condition="context/nativename">)</tal:has_nativename>
    in Launchpad.
    </h1>

    <tal:not-visible condition="not:context/visible">
      This language is not usually displayed in lists of languages. You will
      have to select it specially in your <a href="/+editmylanguages">language
      preferences</a> in order to see it.
    </tal:not-visible>

    <div class="left">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="portlet">
          <h2>Plural Forms</h2>
          <p>
            When translating into this language, you need to be able to
            express plural forms effectively. The plural form expression tells
            the translation system when to use each plural form. For example,
            some languages express the idea of "zero objects" differently to
            "one object" or "more than ten objects". In these cases, the
            plural form expression captures the information needed to know
            which form to use based on the number in question.
          </p>
          <tal:has_pluralforms condition="context/pluralexpression">
            <p>
              The amount of plural forms for
              <tal:language replace="view/language_name">
                Espa&ntilde;ol
              </tal:language>
              is:
              <tal:pluralforms replace="context/pluralforms">
                2
              </tal:pluralforms>
            </p>
            <p>
              And its default plural form expression is:
            </p>
            <p>
              <pre tal:content="context/pluralexpression">
                n != 1
              </pre>
            </p>
          </tal:has_pluralforms>
          <tal:has_not_pluralforms condition="not:context/pluralexpression">
            <p class="helpwanted">
              Unfortunately, Launchpad doesn't know the plural form
              information for this language. If you know it, please open a
              <a href="/rosetta/+addticket">ticket</a> with that information,
              so we can add it to Launchpad.
            </p>
          </tal:has_not_pluralforms>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <div class="portlet">
          <h2>Translation teams</h2>
          <p tal:condition="view/translation_teams">
            The following people and teams are specifically identified as
            being experts in
            <tal:language replace="view/language_name">
              Espa&ntilde;ol
            </tal:language>
            :
          </p>
          <table>
            <tr tal:repeat="expert_info view/translation_teams">
              <td>
                <img tal:condition="expert_info/expert/isTeam"
                     src="/@@/team" />
                <img tal:condition="not:expert_info/expert/isTeam"
                     src="/@@/person" />
              </td>
              <td>
                <div>
                  <a
                    tal:attributes="
                      href expert_info/expert/fmt:url;
                      title expert_info/expert/displayname/fmt:shorten/80"
                    tal:content="expert_info/expert/displayname"
                    >Expert name</a>(
                    <tal:groups repeat="group expert_info/groups">
                      <a tal:attributes="
                           href group/fmt:url;
                           title group/title/fmt:shorten/80"
                         tal:content="group/title"
                         >Translation group title</a>
                    </tal:groups>)
                </div>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p tal:condition="not:view/translation_teams">
            <tal:language replace="view/language_name">
              Espa&ntilde;ol
            </tal:language>
            has no team or person registered as an expert.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="right">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="portlet">
          <h2>Countries</h2>
          <tal:has_countries condition="context/countries">
            <p>
              <tal:language replace="view/language_name">
                Espa&ntilde;ol
              </tal:language>
                is registered as being spoken in the following countries:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li tal:repeat="country context/countries"
                  tal:content="country/name">Spain</li>
            </ul>
          </tal:has_countries>
          <tal:has_not_countries condition="not:context/countries">
          <p class="helpwanted">
            <tal:language replace="view/language_name">
              Espa&ntilde;ol
            </tal:language>
            is not registered as being spoken in any country. If you know
            about a country that officially speaks this language, please
            open a <a href="/rosetta/+addticket">ticket</a> with that
            information, so we can add it to Launchpad.
          </p>
          </tal:has_not_countries>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section"
           tal:content="structure context/@@+portlet-top-contributors" />
    </div>
  </div>
  </body>
</html>
